urds, their continuous resistance for nationhood in their history, and their modern reinventing of the self. An overview of some of the works in modern Kurdish literature points to both asymmetry and commonality in comparative literary studies. These works highight the thematic reach in Kurdish literary studies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKurdish literature. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh  aKurdish Feminist Literature.  aKurdish Studies.  aModern Kurdish Literature.  aNationhood and Literature.1 aAlhamid, Lolav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlsancakli, Sacha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBelçim Galip, Özlem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBullock, Jon E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabi, Marouf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChyet, Michael L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuad Hussain, Shilan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorangy, Alireza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorangy, Alireza, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMortezaee, Mahlagha, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVatanpour, Azadeh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEB